data.title: Sturdy and effective.
data.body: let's face it, boxes are not sexy. Boxes are utility items that you need to be sturdy and you need to be easy to fold and will hold the tape that you close them with and not fall apart. When a person is moving from one house to another, you don't wants to have to worry about the quality of your moving products. I made a move of about 2,000 miles and these boxes held up extremely well in over 2 weeks of being shipped in pods. The tape stayed gripped to the boxes even though we used three different brands of tape. I am very very happy with the purchase. They worked much better than collecting boxes from the local liquor store or supermarket.

data.title: I ordered pack of 12 and received pack of 6
data.body: I wanted to give 1 star because of my inconvenience but the boxes are actually nicely price and are pretty good quality. I gave 3 stars because I ordered these boxes clearly because my family was moving. They came in one day but I didn’t open it until I was ready to start packing 2 days later and I day prior to my move to realize I only received 6 boxes. I called to see if the additional 6 could be sent out overnight. I was told they could only refund me half the amount since I received half of the product. So now I was stuck with 6 freaking boxes and I move tomorrow and now I will be scrambling around trying to find or buy expensive ass boxes…..such an inconvenience and unnecessary stressor amongst all the other obstacles you have to deal with while moving!

data.title: Basic boxes
data.body: We recently moved and needed a ton of boxes to do so. These boxes were actually really thin and I don’t recommend them for heavy things. Smaller boxes are better for heavy objects. I used these mainly for clothing. I recommend taping the bottom of the boxes in addition to folding them to create a seal. There also aren’t handles on the boxes which makes moving them more difficult. I personally like the Home Depot boxes they have extra strength options that can lift a lot of things. These boxes also don’t have an area to mark what room the stuff goes to but that’s not that big of a deal. For the price and convenience these are a good option but I still recommend going to Home Depot.

data.title: Perfect size, sturdy, good value
data.body: I’m moving a small apartment and needed boxes. These large boxes are spacious enough for clothing, kitchenware, books, and all the little items from the bathroom, living room, etc. They are not so big as to be inordinately heavy with judicious packing. The bottom is sturdy with just packing tape, no sign of giving way with even the few heavier boxes. Overall the cardboard is strong and I feel secure packing valuables in these boxes.

However, they would make excellent moving or storage boxes.

data.title: Received After We Moved
data.body:
Part 1: (please read both parts)
Not their fault I don’t think. The boxes were supposed to arrive the day we flew in to pack. Every day I would get a notice they were behind but we needed them so purchased boxes at Home Depot and UHaul.
Finally showed up 6 days later and we left the night before. I would definitely order them 2 weeks before needed.
Part 2:
They are great boxes for a very good price! We bought the same ones to pack another house and they are just as good as the spendy UHaul boxes.

data.title: Bigger than expected
data.body: Very big, very sturdy, but a bit too big. I end up loading too much into each box and two became too heavy to lift. Overall very good value. One thing they can improve is to add holding holes on the side otherwise these are really hard to move alone.

data.title: Boxes work fine but some arrived damaged
data.body: Nine of the boxes are fine but three are totally unusable due to damage. The bundle of 12 boxes was firmly strapped together and placed in a bigger box that had no dents or damage on it, but the strapped bundle had maybe been water damaged or something before being boxed for shipping; along one long edge the cardboard was all curled up, still tucked firmly within the strapping. Someone should have spotted this before shipping. Not worth returning but I am unhappy that 25% of my order is unusable.
